# README
- this is a simple research pipeline example
- it allows to run the entire process from data querying / preparation to a ready-to-submit manuscript without switching software
- it allows the entire process to be easily reproduced with alternative cut-offs, definitions, subsets etc.
- it accomodates the option to be run on small samples for the sake of speed and simplicity 
- at the same time, it allows to run all code segments to be run easily in batch modes (i.e. National Safe Haven settings) when the process is time and memory consuming
- for server setups, we typically need to find a work-around for pandoc when creating our final output
